# EXPERIMENT – 06  
## SQL Queries using Functions 

---

### Aim
To study and execute SQL queries using CASE function, date functions, string functions and arithmetic operations on the EMPLOYEE table.



---

### Table Used
EMPLOYEE

---

### Queries

**1. Display empno, ename and department name using CASE**
```sql
SELECT empno, ename,
CASE deptno
 WHEN 10 THEN 'RESEARCH'
 WHEN 20 THEN 'ACCOUNTING'
 WHEN 30 THEN 'SALES'
 WHEN 40 THEN 'OPERATIONS'
 ELSE 'UNKNOWN'
END AS dept_name
FROM employee;

##2.display age in days
SELECT DATEDIFF(CURDATE(), '2006-10-12') AS age_in_days;

##3display age in months
SELECT TIMESTAMPDIFF(MONTH, '2004-10-12', CURDATE()) AS age_in_months;

###4. Display current date in the format

SELECT DATE_FORMAT(CURDATE(), '%D %M %W %Y') AS formatted_date;
##5. Display output for each employee
SELECT CONCAT(ename, ' earns ', sal, ' salary') AS output
FROM employee;
##6. Display joining details of SCOTT
SELECT CONCAT(
       ename,
       ' has joined the company on ',
       DATE_FORMAT(hiredate, '%W %D %M %Y')
) AS joining_details
FROM employee
WHERE ename = 'SCOTT';
##7. Find the nearest Saturday after the current date
SELECT DATE_ADD(
       CURDATE(),
       INTERVAL (6 - DAYOFWEEK(CURDATE())) DAY
) AS next_saturday;
##8. Display current time
SELECT CURTIME() AS curr_time;
##9. Display the date three months before the current date
SELECT DATE_SUB(CURDATE(), INTERVAL 3 MONTH) AS date_before_3_months;
##10. Display employees who joined in December
SELECT *
FROM employee
WHERE MONTH(hiredate) = 12;
##11. Display employees whose first two characters of hiredate
SELECT *
FROM employee
WHERE LEFT(hiredate, 2) = RIGHT(sal, 2);
##12. Display employees whose 10% of salary equals the year of joining
SELECT *
FROM employee
WHERE (sal * 0.10) = YEAR(hiredate);
##13. Display employees who joined before the 15th of the month
SELECT *
FROM employee
WHERE DAY(hiredate) < 15;
##14. Display employees who joined before the 15th of the month (alternate)
SELECT *
FROM employee
WHERE DAYOFMONTH(hiredate) < 15;
##15. Display employees whose joining day is equal to deptno
SELECT *
FROM employee
WHERE DAY(hiredate) = deptno;


